The '''Business Model of Intercultural Analysis (BMIA)''' is a tool{{Clarify|reason=what sort of tool?|date=November 2013}} developed to address [[cross-cultural]] problems. The BMIA framework uses six comprehension lenses to analyze cross-cultural interaction in the business environment.<ref>{{cite web|author=Diversity Executive |url=http://www.nxtbook.com/nxtbooks/mediatec/de_20120304/#/46 |title=Business without Borders - Diversity Executive |publisher= Diversity Executive |date=2012-03-14 |accessdate=2012-03-14}}</ref> The six comprehension lenses to examine enterprise-wide cross cultural challenges are cultural themes, communication, group dynamics, ‘glocalization,’ process engineering, and time orientation. <ref>{{cite web|author=Profit Magazine |url=http://www.oracle.com/us/corporate/profit/opinion/050312-dhummel-1614961.html |title=Understanding the Importance of Culture in Global Business |publisher= Profit Magazine |date=2012-05-15 |accessdate=2012-05-15}}</ref>
