'''''My Tribe Is My Life''''' (French: '''''Ma tribu c'est ma vie''''') is an interactive [[web documentary]] produced in [[Montreal]] by the [[National Film Board of Canada]] (NFB), which explores how [[young people]] use the [[internet]] to forge identities and relationships within various music [[subcultures]]. Directed by [[Myriam Verreault]] (''[[:fr:À l'ouest de Pluton|À l'ouest de Pluton]]''), the project follows eight people from across the province of [[Quebec]] who have found [[virtual communities]] through the Web.<ref name=Desautels>{{cite news|last=Désautels|first=Michel|title=Ma tribu, c'est ma vie, un webdocumentaire sur les réseaux sociaux|url=http://www.radio-canada.ca/emissions/desautels/2010-2011/chronique.asp?idChronique=133791|accessdate=7 April 2011|newspaper=[[Première Chaîne]]|date=9 February 2011|location=Montreal|language=French|format=Radio interview}}</ref><ref name=Scott-Stevenson>{{cite news|last=Scott-Stevenson|first=Julia|title=My Tribe is My Life|url=http://www.sbs.com.au/documentary/blogs/view/id/122732/t/My-Tribe-is-My-Life|accessdate=7 April 2011|newspaper=[[Special Broadcasting Service]]|date=15 March 2011|location=Australia}}</ref><ref name=voir>{{cite news|last=Laveaux|first=Olivier Robillard|title=Le meilleur ami de l'homme|url=http://www.voir.ca/publishing/article.aspx?zone=1&section=11&article=75597|accessdate=7 April 2011|newspaper=[[Voir]]|date=17 February 2011|location=Montreal|language=French}}</ref> 

Web users watch videos about the eight protagonists, along with survey questions, statistics and quotes. The site features live streaming music, and users can also create their own online [[Avatar (computing)|avatar]]s.<ref name=Scott-Stevenson/>

The idea for a web documentary about online musical communities was conceived by NFB interactive producer [[Hugues Sweeney]].<ref name=lapresse>{{cite news|last=Côté|first=Émilie|title=Ma tribu, c'est ma vie : nouveau documentaire web interactif|url=http://www.cyberpresse.ca/arts/201102/09/01-4368406-ma-tribu-cest-ma-vie-nouveau-documentaire-web-interactif.php|accessdate=7 April 2011|newspaper=[[La Presse (Canadian newspaper)|La Presse]]|date=9 February 2011|location=Montreal|language=French}}</ref>''My Tribe Is My Life'' was produced by Sweeney and web designer Alex Leduc of Atelier Deux Huit Huit.<ref name="NFB">{{cite press release | url=http://www.onf-nfb.gc.ca/eng/press-room/press-releases.php?id=20169 | title=The NFB launches Ma tribu, c'est ma vie, an interactive Web documentary | accessdate=April 7, 2011 | date=February 10, 2011 | publisher=[[National Film Board of Canada]]}}</ref>

''My Tribe Is My Life'' received the grand prize for best experimental website at the 2011 Concours Boomerang, honouring Quebec interactive media.<ref name="Concours Boomerang">{{cite web|title=Grand Prix|url=http://resultats.infopresse.com/prixboomerang/2011/Resultats/sites_internet/sites_experientiel/gp_onf_tribu.html|work=Concours Boomerang|publisher=Les Éditions Infopresse|accessdate=6 April 2012|language=French}}</ref>

