Created in 1995, '''Publifolha''', Grupo Folha’s book-publishing division, has released more than 1,000 titles and currently has 600 books in print.

Its first book was “Primeira Página”, a collection of front pages from newspapers ''Folha da Manhã'', ''Folha da Noite'' and [[Folha de S. Paulo]] since 1921.This title’s latest reprint, issued in February 2011, offers 223 pages, with covers from 1921 to 2010.

Publifolha concentrates on the news, tourism, languages, general reference, children’s tales and cooking areas. 
It is currently the leading travel guide publisher in Brazil, thanks mainly to the “Visual Guide” series, which offers accurate information about countries, cities and regions, with travel itineraries and leisure suggestions for tourists.

